      "content": "1. Boil the pasta in salted water while chopping garlic and adding chili flakes to olive oil.\n2. Drain the pasta and toss it with the garlic-chili-olive oil mixture.\n3. Stir in parmesan cheese and more pasta water to create a creamy sauce.\n4. Add fresh pasta and garlic again to ensure maximum flavor.\n5. Finish with extra parmesan cheese and chili flakes for the perfect score.",
